title: For Sale:  Custom Built WASR
postcontent:
Hey guys up for sale is one of my favorite AK variants.
It's a WASR built by Sure Survival in tampa, unlike other WASRs of it's class thing one does have dimples in the magwell, and the receiver is of higher quality.
I've taken good care of it for the two years I've had it and have only put 500 rounds of Golden Tiger through it, and it does have some light wear marks that are only cosmetic.
In general I've found it to be significantly more accurate than the run of the mill WASR or OPAP, and the sights are perfectly in alignment.
It comes with the pictured 30 round yugo bolt hold open magazine, along with two 5 rounders, and an awesome chicom 40 round steel mag, seriously I love this mag.

ALSO!

For your consideration I'm also pairing this with a Tokarev Pistol chambered in 7.62.
The Pistol is in FANTASTIC condition with no rounds through it at all.
If you're a big Romania fan or just want a good combloc pistol to pair with this excellent combloc rifle then you've come to the right place.
The Pistol itself comes with 2 magazines, a holster, lanyard, and cleaning rod.
The action is very smooth and the pistol still has that out of the box cosmoline smell to it.
From what I've experienced these pistols are the combloc equivalent of the 1911 but with a significantly hotter round. 

Anyway, on to pricing.

I'm asking $700 for the rifle, since it is a higher quality gun in general, that includes all of the magazines and case. If you don't want / need some of the magazines we can negotiate (Also if you're from a ban state that can be a dilemma).

And I'm asking $250 for the pistol, which includes everything pictured and a cardboard box if you decide to just get the pistol.

Now to the good part, if you decide to get both of these awesome guns together I'll set the price at $1000 flat for you. That includes everything listed above. Finally if you're interested I do have some golden tiger left over if you want to add to your purchase, but only if you're buying the rifle or the combo.

Thanks for checking out my listing and I hope to hear from you soon!

EDIT: Hey guys I sold the Tokarev already and only have the WASR left. Also price reduction.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Hypertech Power Programmer for anything with the LT1
postcontent:
Increasing horsepower and torque is as simple as pushing a button with Hypertech's Power Programmer III! You simply plug the Power Programmer into the underdash diagnostic plug, answer a series of "Yes/No" questions, and the Power Programmer does the rest. The Power Programmer is much more than a tuning chop - it is a self-contained automotive tuning computer. 
When you connect the Power Programmer to your vehicle, its "smart" program instantly recognized your vehicle's powertrain by reading its Vehicle Identification Number (VIN). The VIN contains specific information on the engine, transmission, and drivetrain, which the Power Programmer decodes before it downloads the Power Tuning program that is precisely tailored to your car or truck. 

The Power Programmer lets you choose Hypertech's Power Tuning program for regular 87 octane or premium 93 octane gasoline. Both options improve performance without detonation. After the tuning program is selected, the Programmer automatically installs the tuning program, and allows you to access and reprogram the vehicle's computer to function properly with aftermarket components such as non-stock tire sizes and rear-end gear ratios. 

The Power Programmer is incredibly powerful, but it is also incredibly easy to use. Reprogramming does not require any tools or knowledge of cars or even computers - plus you can return to OEM stock programming in just minutes. 

FEATURES (depending on year, make, and model) 

Hypertech Power Tuning: 
Tunes the engine for maximum power and performance, plus potential gas mileage improvements. 
Dual Fuel Tuning 
Lets you choose tuning for 87 octane or 93 octane fuel 
Engine Rev Limiter 
Extends the engines RPM range for a wider power band 
Cooling Fan On/Off Temperatures 
Permits use of low-temperature thermostat for cooler, denser intake charge and lower engine operating temperature 
Transmission Shift Points 
Optimizes shift points by speed and RPM for maximum acceleration 
Transmission Shift Firmness 
Firmer full-throttle gear changes for faster acceleration 
Top-Speed Limiter
Allows the vehicle's top speed to be matched to the speed rating of high-performance tires 
Speedometer/Odometer Correction 
Automatically corrects speedometer and odometer readings with non-stock tire sizes and/or non-stock rear-end gear ratios (accurate odometer readings are required by law) "

title: For Sale:  Americas truck for Americans! A 1969 Chevy C10 4x4
postcontent:
Up for sale I have a 1969 C10 4x4 that was built for Uncle Sam when the Cold War was on every American's mind, in every American's home and all over the evening news. This beast was designed by Americans who built the Atomic Bomb, built to support our troops, to resupply them in the heat of battle, and to power forward when lives and country are on the line. This truck was forged in the Heartland of America built from recycled tanks and bombers in a time when STEEL was on the road to not just protect you from an accident but survive and drive you home!
Luckily Former President Ronald Reagan ended the Cold War giving us civilians a chance to drive a beast meant for the heat of battle but tame enough for Americas roads.
It's a stick shift built for that farmboy drafted to be a soldier, one who knows his way around mighty machines that tear at the land and feed a hungry country. 
There is no rust or rot as both fear to even try to form, and with its all American STEEL body she's as straight as an Arrow shot from the bow of Geronimo himself.
Born with a 350 V8 there is NO fancy namby pamby computer crap or sensors to choke life from this mighty machine. Which means you can bust out those Craftsman's tools your beautiful wife/girlfriend bought you for Valentines Day as a symbol of love and wrench on her yourself!
Here's a little 411 directly from Chevy on the engine that beats under the hood of this monster:
The L-48 is the original 350 cu in (5.7 L), solely available for 1967 in the Super Sport version of Camaro SS 350 (1967-up) or Chevy II/Nova in '68-79. In '69 it was used in almost all car lines; Camaros, Impalas, El Caminos, Chevelles & Novas. 1969 L-48's use a Hyd Cam, 4bbl Quadrajet carburetor, cast pistons, 4-bolt main casting number 010 Blocks & casting number 041 or 186 heads. Power output was 300HP and 380 lb·ft (520 N·m) torque. Compression ratio was 10.25:1.
Now take a moment to soak all that information in... An engine so powerful that it powered other champions and still does half a century later! We're talking cars with pedigree's only Legend's can drive!
Tear down trees, rip houses from their foundations, cause your neighbor's Prius to spontaneously combust by merely passing him on the freeway. Did I say freeway! That's RIGHT son of Paul Bunyan, drive her on America's freeways and highways! Keeping her away from those commie states who take your hard earned American money.
This is an AMERICAN truck meant for AMERICANS! God fearing, steak eating, gun shooting warriors of the back woods! This is that EMP proof, bullet proof monster to get you out of dodge in! Taking family and gear to your bug out location and doing it in classic style!
Now it's hard to put a price on American muscle like this! But with a growing family I need to pass her on to another worthy red blooded American who can appreciate power. A man or woman able to control this beast and love it as much as I have.
If you think you measure up shoot me an email and I'll introduce you.

Many parts are included along with a bed mounted tool drawer to keep your tow chains, double-bit axe and bowie knife safe in any weather! And the final item that should push you over is a 100 amp alternator pulsating, feeding unimaginable power to your whim! This means you can put a winch on her or install off road lights or anything else your imagination can conjure up!

WHAT ARE YOU WAITING FOR! Americas roads needs you! Your honey do list can finally be completed!
